-- Fininvest Says Berlusconi's Company Structure `Transparent,' Denies Report
-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 2010-09-28T10:12:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/fininvest-says-berlusconi-s-company-structure-transparent-denies-report.html
Fininvest SpA, Italian Prime
Minister Silvio Berlusconi’s holding company, said its company
structure is “clear and transparent,” according to an e-mailed
statement.  The company responded to a press report on La Repubblica,
it said. Fininvest denied that offshore companies or accounts
are linked to the company, according to the statement. Fininvest
is considering legal action against the newspaper, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Bertacche at 
 mbertacche@bloomberg.net  